# Repo-root `.env` — copy to `.env`. This file only feeds tools that read
# `process.env`: drizzle-kit (packages/db/drizzle.config.ts) and the
# wrangler CLI. The dev Worker's own config comes off the Cloudflare `env`
# binding, so its secrets live in `apps/web/.dev.vars` — see
# `apps/web/.dev.vars.example`.

# Cloudflare D1 (set via wrangler.jsonc binding for runtime; these are for drizzle-kit)
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=""
CLOUDFLARE_DATABASE_ID=""
CLOUDFLARE_D1_TOKEN=""
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=""

# Everything else the app needs at runtime — BETTER_AUTH_SECRET, the R2
# keys, FAL_API_KEY — is a Worker binding, not a process env var. Put those
# in `apps/web/.dev.vars` (locally) or `wrangler secret put` (production).
